page.title: 01LANDSCAPE
page.content: LANDSCAPE The area is a quiet undulating country area,much of it covered by woodland. Pine trees,silver birch,oak trees are predominant,but holly,rhododendrun and beech are also found.The soil is sandy especially near the Devil's Jumps and Frensham Pond;fern and bracken cover the ground under the trees and over the common,there is a wide variety of wild flowers growing undisturbed.At one time in June as many as 250 different varieties of wild flower were counted. Butterflies and moths also abound in great variety,while birds such as yellow hammer,redwing chiff-chaff,heron can be seen as well as the more common ones.Foxes and deer are also often seen. Farmland covers the second largest area of land,while housing accounts for only a small percentage.
